<item>
            <title>[CODEC-229] StringUtils.newStringxxx(null) should return null, not NPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-229</link>
                <project id="12310464" key="CODEC">Commons Codec</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Method calls such as StringUtils.newStringIso8859_1(null) should return null, not NPE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this capability was lost with the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-136&quot; title=&quot;Use Charset objects when possible, create Charsets class for required character encodings&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CODEC-136&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CODEC-136&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, i.e.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1306366&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1306366&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Several methods were changed from&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; StringUtils.newString(bytes, CharEncoding.xxx);
to
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;(bytes, Charsets.xxx);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new code should have been:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; newString(bytes, Charsets.xxx);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The newString method handles null input.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There were no tests for null input so the change in behaviour was missed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
